    "body": "I think we're seeing this manifest in errors like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nNov 03 06:30:51.979 WARN BlockProcessingFailure                  outcome: ObservedAttestationsError(IncorrectSlot { expected: Slot(511412), attestation: Slot(511411) }), msg: unexpected condition in processing block.\r\n```\r\n\r\nBecause at the moment methods like `ObservedAttestations::observe_attestation` lock the datastructure to compute an index to mutate at, release the lock (allow concurrent mutation and shifting of the relevant index), and then mutate anyway at the precomputed index:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/0cde4e285ccd021f2564e0474b6dc981e5b5faa9/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/observed_attestations.rs#L138-L151",
